Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.02,0:00:04.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnArial Black\pos(316,325)\fad(400,0)}Obey the Rules and manners\Nto have a fun Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.97,0:00:20.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Light so glaring that it can't be hidden shatters the silence and revives in this world
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.98,0:00:31.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The violently quaking and thirsty Earth stakes its life and clashes together with sparks
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.74,0:00:38.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Just one more time is enough to create a miracle
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.96,0:00:45.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For the power to regain the pages of memory lost in the past
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.88,0:00:54.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1\fs30}The believing heart that penetrates the darkness searches for the place where its soul sleeps
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.18,0:01:00.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And burns a sharp glance of eyes that can't sparkle
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.56,0:01:07.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Two hearts of light and shadow head toward the future that the crystal reflects
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.90,0:01:14.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now they start to move, these eyes brimming red
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.90,0:01:31.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's finally the Final Match of the KC Grand Prix.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.19,0:01:34.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The match was supposed to be between Leon-{\i0}kun{\i1} and Sieg...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.11,0:01:38.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But Kaiba-{\i0}kun{\i1} suddenly appeared and disqualified Sieg!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.61,0:01:43.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And he arranged for himself to play in the Final instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.33,0:01:47.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sieg attacks Kaiba-{\i0}kun{\i1} with a heart full of rivalry...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.46,0:01:49.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Just how will this Duel end?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.54,0:01:57.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Valkyries VS Blue-Eyes White Dragon"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.97,0:02:03.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaiba...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.06,0:02:07.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The curse of the Valkyries has just yet begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.14,0:02:09.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Due to the effects of Nibelung's Ring...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.48,0:02:11.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can draw two cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.94,0:02:17.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If any Monster Cards are drawn, one must be discarded to the Cemetery.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.82,0:02:20.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Humph! What kind of curse is {\i1}that{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.61,0:02:22.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.91,0:02:26.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No Monster Card.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.00,0:02:28.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I place one reverse card and end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.83,0:02:34.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph. Still, you cannot control the XYZ-Dragon Cannon you have on the field
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.84,0:02:39.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,due to the effect of Nibelung's Ring...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.51,0:02:41.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he going to Direct Attack again?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.97,0:02:44.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is my turn! I draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.60,0:02:45.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I come, Kaiba!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.60,0:02:49.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I use Valkyrie Zwei to Direct Attack the player!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.69,0:02:56.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reverse card, open! Attack Guidance Armor!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.07,0:03:02.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your attack will be guided to the Monster equipped with this armor!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.53,0:03:05.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reverse card, open!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.49,0:03:07.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wotan's Judgment!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.96,0:03:14.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card can be activated when a Monster attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.54,0:03:21.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By exchanging a Magic Card in my hand with the topmost card on the deck,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.13,0:03:23.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Battle Phase will be forced to end.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.47,0:03:27.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Such a pathetic tactic.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.60,0:03:34.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But thanks to you, I now have all the Goddesses of Fate in my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.31,0:03:36.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Watch this!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.19,0:03:37.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Continuous Magic...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.32,0:03:40.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goddess Urd's Verdict!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.61,0:03:43.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goddess Verdandi's Guidance!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.16,0:03:45.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goddess Skuld's Oracle!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.20,0:03:48.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those three goddesses have appeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.49,0:03:52.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the Monster Erasing Combo that caused Jounouchi-{\i1}kun{\i0} to squirm...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.37,0:03:56.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A small trick to seal the opponent's hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.59,0:03:58.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A move fitting for a rat like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.63,0:04:00.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you would be mistaken there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.17,0:04:06.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As I am favored ever-so by fate, I am able to forgive your petty insults.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.05,0:04:08.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goddess Skuld, the one that controls the future...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.85,0:04:12.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Show me the future that is to come!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.11,0:04:20.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Three Blue-Eyes White Dragons?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.36,0:04:23.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you looking so nervous?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.32,0:04:25.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you seen the fate that will destroy you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.49,0:04:29.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That will be all for the moment! Do not attack him!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.37,0:04:31.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Due to the effect of Goddess Verdandi's Guidance,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.91,0:04:33.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can know the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.08,0:04:36.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll guess the topmost card of your deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.88,0:04:38.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a Monster Card!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.09,0:04:44.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I am right, please Summon the Monster in face-down Defense Position.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.63,0:04:47.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Worthless trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.01,0:04:54.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, Goddess Urd, the one who controls the past, will pass judgment on the card!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.06,0:04:57.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If guessed correctly, the card will be removed from the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.94,0:05:00.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Vorher{\i0}! Begin your journey towards Valhalla!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.44,0:05:02.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blue-Eyes White Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.45,0:05:12.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blue-Eyes...!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.41,0:05:13.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Disappeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.20,0:05:15.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.12,0:05:18.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaiba.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.29,0:05:23.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Your superb luck in drawing cards will become your downfall.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.17,0:05:26.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When the two Blue-Eyes are drawn later...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.34,0:05:30.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}One will be sent to the Cemetery due to the effect of Nibelung's Ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.76,0:05:33.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And then, due to the Special Effect of Erste...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.97,0:05:37.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It will take on the same Attack Power of the Blue-Eyes in the Cemetery.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.81,0:05:41.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If Erste gets on the Fortune Chariot to attack...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.73,0:05:43.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...you will come to meet your end.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.65,0:05:45.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.57,0:05:46.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.28,0:05:50.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaiba, I am well aware.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.20,0:05:56.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Due to Nibelung's Ring's effect, the Monster Card you've drawn gets sent to the Cemetery!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.08,0:06:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now I simply wait for him to declare his turn's end!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.00,0:06:05.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate Resurrection of the Dead from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.92,0:06:07.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.13,0:06:09.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Return from the Graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.01,0:06:11.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come out, Blue-Eyes White Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.68,0:06:17.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You did it, Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.39,0:06:18.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's finally appeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.69,0:06:22.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Blue-Eyes won't let you do as you please!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.02,0:06:25.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blue-Eyes, attack Valkyrie Zwei!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.48,0:06:28.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Burst Stream of Destruction!!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.28,0:06:37.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fortune Chariot will be sacrificed in order to prevent Valkyrie Zwei's destruction!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.16,0:06:39.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.71,0:06:41.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now their Life Points are equal!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.63,0:06:43.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.25,0:06:46.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph, what was that about being favored by fate?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.09,0:06:49.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that were true, it would be on the side of Blue-Eyes White Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.47,0:06:52.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.47,0:06:55.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Effect of the Three Goddesses!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.60,0:07:03.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Place the third card on the top of the deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.94,0:07:08.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That card is a Monster Card!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.69,0:07:11.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be gone, Emerald Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.41,0:07:21.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next from my hand, I activate the Magic Card, Gryphon's Feather Duster.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.17,0:07:28.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By destroying all the Magic and Trap Cards I have on my field,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.63,0:07:32.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I regain 500 Life Points for every card.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.64,0:07:37.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just when Blue-Eyes managed to deal him some damage...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.81,0:07:43.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next, I sacrifice Valkyrie Erste and Valkyrie Zwei...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.27,0:07:50.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To Summon Valkyrie Brunnhilde in Defense Position!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.49,0:08:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.00,0:08:03.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaiba, I hate to steal away your anticipation of the next card you'll draw...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.96,0:08:06.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the first will be a Monster Card.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.25,0:08:08.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph. My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.51,0:08:13.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Activate the effect of Nibelung's Ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.51,0:08:15.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Discard one Monster Card into the Cemetery!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.72,0:08:20.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just one Blue-Eyes will be enough for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.56,0:08:22.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go forth, Blue-Eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.10,0:08:25.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Burst Stream of Destruction!!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.86,0:08:38.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brunnhilde's Special Effect has been activated.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.74,0:08:42.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By losing 1000 Defense Points, she can avoid getting destroyed in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.67,0:08:48.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one card and I end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.42,0:08:50.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quite a pity it is, Kaiba.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.84,0:08:55.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you can't use that effect once her Defense Power reaches zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.34,0:08:57.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I am aware of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.80,0:09:00.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is my turn! I draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.51,0:09:03.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I change Valkyrie Brunnhilde into Attack Position!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.23,0:09:12.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Attack Power of Brunnhilde increases by 300 points for every Dragon-Type Monster on the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.40,0:09:20.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In addition, from my hand, I activate the Equipment Magic, Enchanted Sword Nothung!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.21,0:09:33.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When this sword is equipped, all Dragon-Type Monsters on the opponent's field are removed from the game!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.51,0:09:41.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In just a second, Blue-Eyes got...!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.64,0:09:42.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.56,0:09:47.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the Attack Power of the Monster equipped with this card goes up by 400 points!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.86,0:09:52.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The power of Nothung does not end {\i1}there{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.82,0:09:57.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can destroy all Dragon-Type Monsters in battle and not take any damage at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.53,0:10:00.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, this blade is known as the "Dragon-Slaying Sword"!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.74,0:10:04.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In addition, I activate a Magic Card from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.58,0:10:06.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I invoke Pegasus Wings!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.62,0:10:12.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card can be activated when Fortune Chariot lies in the Cemetery.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.54,0:10:15.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Monster with "Valkyrie" in its name
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.21,0:10:20.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,can Direct Attack the opposing player this turn with half its Attack Power!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.43,0:10:27.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you should also know what the set card I've played is.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.81,0:10:32.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, I'm still able to decrease your Life by 550 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.77,0:10:34.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Brunnhilde!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.69,0:10:37.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack the player directly!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.32,0:10:39.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reverse card, open!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.41,0:10:40.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shrink!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.70,0:10:45.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pay it no mind!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.50,0:10:53.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.98,0:11:15.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The epilogue draws near.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.94,0:11:18.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know how long I've waited for this moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.90,0:11:21.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since the first day I laid my eyes on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.57,0:11:28.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I've wanted you to disappear ever since that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.04,0:11:33.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even back when your father, Gozaburo Kaiba, was still the CEO...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.21,0:11:35.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As both our companies excelled in military trading,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.42,0:11:38.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my Schroeder Company was always under your pressure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.88,0:11:42.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To my father, that was the greatest humiliation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.68,0:11:48.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was unreasonable for the supreme Schroeders
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.14,0:11:49.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to be beaten by a company like yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.48,0:11:55.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As the successor, I wanted to surpass Kaiba Corporation...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.98,0:12:00.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I wanted to surpass the next successor, Seto Kaiba...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.65,0:12:05.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I not only wanted to surpass you, but I wanted to hand you a complete and utter defeat!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.28,0:12:11.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, as my father began to compete against Kaiba Corporation again and again...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.66,0:12:15.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Schroeder Company began to drop in performance day after day.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.96,0:12:21.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My father went crazy from the shock and fatigue and was consumed by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.42,0:12:28.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keeping my father's name intact, I took control of the Schroeder Company as the new CEO.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.06,0:12:33.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The first thing I did was get rid of the military department...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.10,0:12:36.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I entered into a new area of the gaming industry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.81,0:12:39.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was willing to ruin my own life
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.23,0:12:41.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if it meant getting rid of the hatred I had for Kaiba Corporation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.94,0:12:43.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.99,0:12:45.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i0}Herr{\i1} Siegfried!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.45,0:12:48.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kaiba Corporation made an announcement earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.28,0:12:52.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Seto Kaiba has taken over Kaiba Corporation as the new CEO...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.66,0:12:54.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He announced that they would dissolve their military department,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.87,0:12:58.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and go fully into the game development industry!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.25,0:12:59.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Wha-?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.92,0:13:01.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What did you just say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.21,0:13:06.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}After that, in order to walk out of your shadow...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.09,0:13:09.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I devoted myself to game development day after day.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.26,0:13:15.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Finally, the Duel Monsters Duel Box System I had most confidence in
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.14,0:13:17.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was developed successfully.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.06,0:13:20.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.99,0:13:24.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.86,0:13:27.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With the funding of your Solid Vision System...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.28,0:13:29.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a step behind, you stole my chance from me with one shake of your hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.99,0:13:33.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To think that happened...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.33,0:13:38.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But fate is finally smiling down on me now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.29,0:13:41.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that the Kaiba Corporation's stock prices have fallen considerably,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.21,0:13:45.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and my defeating you during this time where civilians have lost trust in your company...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.17,0:13:50.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even Pegasus himself will give up on you and form a new partnership with us Schroeders.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.97,0:13:53.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that your aim?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.89,0:13:57.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaiba, even you cannot deny that
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.10,0:14:00.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the fate of Kaiba Corporation lies on the success of your competition!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.65,0:14:03.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what if it does?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.90,0:14:04.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.94,0:14:09.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You keep going on and on about your hatred for me and all...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.70,0:14:12.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that has absolutely nothing to do with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.53,0:14:17.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those empty words you muttered didn't move me one bit!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.33,0:14:18.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaiba...!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.96,0:14:23.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me show you the difference between us as Duelists!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.88,0:14:26.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.55,0:14:30.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no Monster Card.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.30,0:14:34.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From my hand, I activate a Magic Card, Angel's Charity.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.85,0:14:40.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I draw three cards from the deck and discard two from my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.02,0:14:41.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice thinking!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.27,0:14:44.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that way, he doesn't need to discard any Monster Cards that he drew.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.90,0:14:45.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.86,0:14:49.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Looks like its starting... Kaiba's retaliation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.36,0:14:52.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I discard these two cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.28,0:14:54.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? He's sending Blue-Eyes into the Cemetery?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.95,0:15:00.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In addition, by removing the Blue-Eyes and Pitch-Dark Dragon in my Graveyard from play,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.33,0:15:04.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Chaos Emperor Dragon in Attack Position!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.63,0:15:12.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's useless!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.09,0:15:14.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no dragon that the Enchanted Sword can't conquer!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.56,0:15:18.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, the Special Ability of Chaos Emperor Dragon is that...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.06,0:15:21.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can send all cards in both players' hands and on the field to the Graveyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.77,0:15:27.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But in order to activate that ability, you need to use 1000 Life Points.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.32,0:15:29.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Life Points-
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.19,0:15:30.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one more card!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.37,0:15:37.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In addition, I activate the Quick-Play Magic, Emergency Provisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.49,0:15:43.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get to regain 1000 Life Points by destroying one Magic or Trap Card from on my field.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.79,0:15:45.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.01,0:15:53.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I use 1000 Life Points to activate the Special Effect of Chaos Emperor Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.01,0:15:56.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Destroy everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.93,0:15:59.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cemetery of Fire!!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.86,0:16:14.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This effect also states that you'll be dealt 300 points of damage
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.45,0:16:17.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for every card that got sent to the Graveyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.79,0:16:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.91,0:16:23.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet you can't hear fate whispering to you anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.29,0:16:26.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.42,0:16:28.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From my hand, I activate Pot of Greed!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.76,0:16:33.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I draw two cards from my deck!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.76,0:16:37.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I activate the Continuous Magic from my hand, Magical Alms!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.85,0:16:42.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card allows me to regain 1000 Life Points the moment it's activated.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.81,0:16:48.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In addition, at every turn, each player must predict how many Magic Cards they will use,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.52,0:16:52.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and both players will gain 500 of their Life for each Magic Card that appears.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.99,0:16:55.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, when the number used is less than predicted,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.53,0:16:57.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,both will suffer 1000 points of damage per card.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.91,0:16:59.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I predict that I'll use one card!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.16,0:17:08.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I then activate a Magic Card from my hand, Final Light!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.29,0:17:09.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By paying 1000 Life Points,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.88,0:17:13.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can Special Summon one Light-Attribute Monster from the Cemetery!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.80,0:17:17.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Revive, Brunnhilde!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.76,0:17:25.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The opposing player can also Special Summon one Monster with Attack Points of 2000 or less.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.19,0:17:29.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll Special Summon Grand Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.82,0:17:32.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Due to Brunnhilde's Effect,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.78,0:17:36.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she gains 300 Attack Points for every Dragon-Type Monster on the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.74,0:17:41.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Valkyrie Brunnhilde, attack Grand Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.04,0:17:51.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like the tables have turned, Kaiba.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.75,0:17:53.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.21,0:17:54.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.72,0:17:56.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.05,0:18:00.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I predict that I'll use four Magic Cards!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.39,0:18:04.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Saying that he'll use four when he only has one card on his hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.56,0:18:07.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. I'll destroy you with those four cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.52,0:18:12.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You... seriously believe you can?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.44,0:18:13.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This will be the first!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.69,0:18:17.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From my hand, I activate the Magic Card, Life-Shaving Card Treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.95,0:18:20.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can then draw until I have five cards in my hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.99,0:18:23.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I must discard my entire hand after five turns into the Graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.91,0:18:25.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.96,0:18:28.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The second.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.00,0:18:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From my hand, I activate the Magic Card, Soul Release!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.00,0:18:35.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Both players can select up to five cards from the Graveyard
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.17,0:18:37.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and remove them from the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.01,0:18:40.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I select Chaos Emperor Dragon from the Graveyard and remove it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.43,0:18:42.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The third!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.93,0:18:46.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From my hand, I activate Magic Reproduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.39,0:18:49.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By sending two Magic Cards to the Graveyard,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.14,0:18:52.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get to add one Magic Card from the Graveyard back to my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.65,0:18:56.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the fourth!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.57,0:19:01.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I use 2000 Life Points to activate Dimension Fusion from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.70,0:19:09.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With this, both players may Special Summon all their Monsters removed from play!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.55,0:19:24.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.64,0:19:29.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brunnhilde gains Attack Points for every Dragon you play!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.06,0:19:32.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Against Brunnhilde, no Dragon you play stands a chan-
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.77,0:19:35.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Emerald Dragon, attack Brunnhilde!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.91,0:19:48.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's only got 50 of his Life left!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.00,0:19:48.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.87,0:19:51.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you gone mad, Kaiba?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.25,0:19:57.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As the number of Dragons decreased, Brunnhilde's Attack Power went down!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.38,0:20:01.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chaos Emperor Dragon, attack Brunnhilde!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.39,0:20:13.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brunnhilde can avoid being destroyed by reducing her Defense Power by 1000!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.32,0:20:20.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blue-Eyes White Dragon, attack Brunnhilde!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.32,0:20:23.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Burst Stream of Destruction!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.12,0:20:38.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With that, Brunnhilde can no longer use that Special Ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.21,0:20:42.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blue-Eyes White Dragon, attack Brunnhilde!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.09,0:20:45.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Burst Stream of Destruction!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.22,0:20:51.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My... Valkyrie..!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.19,0:20:55.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My last Blue-Eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.02,0:20:58.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Play a requiem for this miserable, fallen man!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.61,0:21:01.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Direct Attack the player!!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.07,0:21:04.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Burst Stream of Destruction!!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.55,0:21:21.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn you...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.63,0:21:24.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph... In the end, a rat will always be a rat.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.55,0:21:28.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way it could ever beat {\i1}me{\i0}, the king of all animals!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.93,0:21:34.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well done, Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.15,0:21:37.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's amazing...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.14,0:21:59.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}To show us now...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.44,0:22:08.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...a map isn't needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.91,0:22:14.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Only what tore apart the darkness...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.04,0:22:24.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...the hope that lies in my hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.17,0:22:30.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Without deciding on a goal...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.60,0:22:38.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll just take a step toward my dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.23,0:22:44.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}EYE'S, while I feel them...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.69,0:22:52.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll find your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.33,0:22:58.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Oh! EYE'S, if what I wished for...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.54,0:23:06.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...shudders my very soul...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.09,0:23:10.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...a Duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.08,0:23:22.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sieg infiltrated the KC Grand Prix with the intention of ruining it...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.42,0:23:26.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he was utterly defeated by Kaiba-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s relentless attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.05,0:23:27.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As expected!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.26,0:23:28.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to say that...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.67,0:23:33.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I sort of feel sorry for Sieg, seeing him look so dejected.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.80,0:23:36.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, it's time to pit the title of Duel King,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.60,0:23:38.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as the final battle between Yugi and Leon-{\i1}kun{\i0} begins.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.89,0:23:41.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Both of you must do your best!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.23,0:23:41.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.90,0:23:45.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Final Battle for Duel King - Yugi VS Leon"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.19,0:23:46.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel standby!
